// 7. TREND SYNTHESIS
// ============================================================

= Trend Synthesis: Six Shifts in Iranian Doctrine

#v(0.3cm)

== Trend 1: Saturation Over Precision

*TP3:* 550+ ballistic missiles, 1,000+ drones. High per-unit cost, moderate accuracy. \
*TP4:* Drone-led salvos (230+ in a single wave — Wave 16). Low per-unit cost, volume-oriented.

*Evidence:* Drone integration jumped from 32% of waves (TP3) to 83% (TP4). Wave 16 alone launched 230 attack drones — more than the total drone count of many TP3 waves combined.

== Trend 2: Tempo Acceleration

*TP3:* 10.5-hour average gap. \
*TP4:* 5.4-hour average gap — nearly 2× faster.

*Evidence:* TP4's maximum gap (14h) is shorter than TP3's average gap (10.5h). This compression is consistent with pre-positioned assets and solid-fuel dominance eliminating liquid-fuel setup delays.

== Trend 3: Geographic Expansion

*TP3:* 1 country (Israel). \
*TP4:* 12 countries.

*Evidence:* 6 new-country escalation events in TP4's first 11 waves. US bases targeted in 83% of waves — more than Israel (72%). Gulf shipping, Omani ports, and Diego Garcia all struck.

== Trend 4: Shift from Liquid-Fuel to Drone-Led

*TP3:* Emad (91% of waves) and Ghadr (95%) dominated — both liquid-fueled MRBMs. \
*TP4:* Shahed-136 (83% of waves) dominates. Emad dropped to 11%, Ghadr to 17%.

*Evidence:* This shift may reflect inventory depletion after TP3's heavy ballistic missile expenditure, a deliberate cost-exchange strategy, or both. Cruise missiles (3 waves) appeared for the first time.

== Trend 5: Earlier Advanced Weapon Deployment

*TP3:* Advanced systems (Fattah-1, Sejjil, Kheibar Shekan) appeared in waves 11--21 (the campaign's second half). \
*TP4:* Kheibar Shekan appeared at wave 10. Fattah-2 HGV reportedly used by day 2.

*Evidence:* Iran is no longer holding advanced systems in reserve as escalation leverage. They are being integrated earlier, suggesting confidence in their survivability or concern about losing them to preemptive strikes.

== Trend 6: Multi-Domain Integration

*TP3:* Ballistic missiles + drones (supplementary). No cruise missiles. \
*TP4:* Ballistic missiles + drones (primary) + cruise missiles (new). Anti-shipping operations. Drone carrier deployment (IRIS Shahid Bagheri, sunk day 1).

*Evidence:* TP4 represents Iran's first attempt at a truly joint operation: land-based TEL launches, naval drone carrier operations, cruise missile employment, and coordination with Gulf-wide OWA drone swarms. The loss of the Shahid Bagheri on day 1 disrupted the naval component, but the doctrinal intent was multi-domain.

